<HEAD>Ms. Bhutto Says Pakistan Does Not Possess Nuclear Device</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: New material, editing throughout with address to Congress.</HEAD>
<HEAD>Laserphoto WX7</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By SUSANNE M. SCHAFER</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Prime Minister <PERSON> Benazir </PERSON> <PERSON> Bhutto </PERSON> of <LOCATION> Pakistan </LOCATION> told a joint meeting of <ORGANIZATION> Congress </ORGANIZATION> today that <LOCATION> Pakistan </LOCATION> does not possess a nuclear weapon, will not build one and `` will not provoke a nuclear arms race'' on the Indian subcontinent. Ms. <PERSON> Bhutto </PERSON> made her pledge in an address in which she said democracy is on the rise in her region and dictators are in retreat around the world. She said the <ORGANIZATION> United </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> State </ORGANIZATION> and <LOCATION> Pakistan </LOCATION> represent a partnership for democracy that must redouble its efforts to bring a broad-based, democratic government to war-scarred <LOCATION> Afghanistan </LOCATION>. `` <LOCATION> Pakistan </LOCATION> and the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> have traveled a long road with <LOCATION> Afghanistan </LOCATION> in quest of self determination,'' the Pakistani prime minister said. She said that now that Soviet forces have withdrawn, `` let us not leave with indifference, we must not abandon the cause.'' Turning to the most active concern voiced in the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> about her country's conduct, Ms. <PERSON> Bhutto </PERSON> said <LOCATION> Pakistan </LOCATION> has no intention of becoming a nuclear weapons power. `` I can declare that we do not possess nor do we intend to make a nuclear device,'' the Pakistani prime minister said. She said her government is ready to accept international safeguards on its nuclear materials and reactors `` on a non-discriminatory regional basis.'' <LOCATION> Pakistan </LOCATION> has long advocated a nuclear-free zone in the region, Ms. <PERSON> Bhutto </PERSON> said, adding that her country is prepared to conclude a nuclear test ban with neighbors in <LOCATION> South </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Asia </LOCATION>. She mentioned no other country. <LOCATION> Pakist