<HEAD>Girl Sets Herself on Fire</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BULAWAYO, Zimbabwe (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A girl who squandered her school fees on makeup, clothing and candy died after dousing herself with paraffin and setting herself alight, police said Wednesday. <PERSON> Gift </PERSON> <PERSON> Nhliziyo </PERSON>, 18, of <ORGANIZATION> Tekwane </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> High </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> School </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Bulawayo </LOCATION>, locked herself in her family's suburban home before striking the match, on Saturday, police said. Neighbors forced their way into the house by wrenching out burglar bars after hearing the girl's screams. The girl was rushed to hospital where she later died. Her brother said she committed suicide after being sent home from school because she spent a term's fees, equivalent to $ 140.
