<HEAD>Videos Showing Violence Banned Under Revised Swiss Code</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BERN, Switzerland (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Parliament on Wednesday banned videos and sound recordings that show excessive violence. The National Council, the lower house, unanimously approved a revision of the penal code to set unspecified jail terms or fines for violators of the violence ban. The article covers sound and visual recordings, as well as pictures that obviously feature violence against humans or animals without any artistic or scientific value.
