<HEAD>Bush `Disgusted' by Document on Foley Record</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: Subs 6th graf, Fitzwater said, and INSERTS 3 new grafs after
7th graf, ``He was,'' with new Foley, Michel quotes</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By JIM DRINKARD</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 President <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> was `` disgusted'' by a <ORGANIZATION> Republican </ORGANIZATION> document that labeled House Speaker <PERSON> Tom </PERSON> <PERSON> Foley </PERSON> a closet liberal, <PERSON> Bush </PERSON>'s spokesman said today. The author of the memo, meantime, resigned his party post. <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> called <PERSON> Lee </PERSON> <PERSON> Atwater </PERSON>, chairman of the <ORGANIZATION> Republican </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Committee </ORGANIZATION>, to complain about the incident and <PERSON> Atwater </PERSON> apologized to <PERSON> Foley </PERSON>, said presidential press secretary <PERSON> Marlin </PERSON> <PERSON> Fitzwater </PERSON>. `` We consider the matter closed,'' he added. Meanwhile, <PERSON> Mark </PERSON> <PERSON> Goodin </PERSON>, the author of the memo that equated <PERSON> Foley </PERSON>'s voting record with that of Rep. <PERSON> Barney </PERSON> <PERSON> Frank </PERSON>, an acknowledged homosexual, resigned today as <ORGANIZATION> RNC </ORGANIZATION> communications director. <PERSON> Goodin </PERSON> was a press assistant in <PERSON> Bush </PERSON>'s 1988 presidential campaign. <PERSON> Fitzwater </PERSON> said <PERSON> Bush </PERSON>, who had a 90-minute lunch today with <PERSON> Foley </PERSON> and <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION> Republican Leader <PERSON> Bob </PERSON> <PERSON> Michel </PERSON>, had no advance knowledge of the <PERSON> Goodin </PERSON> memo. `` He was disgusted by this entire incident,'' the spokesman said. He said the memo seeking to discredit <PERSON> Foley </PERSON>, D-Wash., violated the spirit of bipartisan cooperation that <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> has advocated since taking office `` The issue is closed,'' <PERSON> Foley </PERSON> said outside the White House. <PERSON> Michel </PERSON>, R-Ill., told reporters, `` There was n't all the kind of oversight there probably should have been'' at the <ORGANIZATION> RNC </ORGANIZATION> `` It was a mist