ralian tourist <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Flitcroft </PERSON>, who was at <LOCATION> Tiananmen </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Square </LOCATION> in <LOCATION> Beijing </LOCATION> when the troops swept out student protesters, said he hid in a dormitory facing the square that night. `` They -LRB- tanks -RRB- crushed the whole square,'' he said. `` They just ran across like a lawnmower, crushing the tents with students in.''
