nfrontation between a Jewish settler and several <LOCATION> Palestinian </LOCATION> women kicked off a melee that ended when an Arab-driven car crashed, seriously injuring the driver and hurting a passenger. The settler, <PERSON> Anat </PERSON> <PERSON> Cohen </PERSON>, told <ORGANIZATION> Israel </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> radio </ORGANIZATION> that `` There was a group of <PERSON> Arab </PERSON> women who cursed us, so I asked them to apologize. They refused, and I hit one.'' Nearby, the Arab-driven car turned around. Settlers told the radio it attempted to run Ms. <PERSON> Cohen </PERSON> down, but <PERSON> Arabs </PERSON> said the driver lost control when he was hit by rubber bullets fired by a soldier. Ms. <PERSON> Cohen </PERSON> was struck by the car, treated for minor leg bruises and released. In the town of <LOCATION> Qalqilya </LOCATION> to the north, masked <PERSON> Arab </PERSON> youths seriously injured a 45-year-old Palestinian woman and her 17-year-old daughter who were accused of aiding Israeli authorities. The women were beaten with clubs and chains and stabbed with a knife, <PERSON> Arab </PERSON> reports said.
