o sentence <PERSON> Rogers </PERSON> to death, jurors had to unanimously find the crimes were deliberate and that the defendant was likely to commit violence again. <PERSON> Rogers </PERSON>' criminal history stretches back to 1972, when he stabbed a 15-year-old girl with a hunting knife. The girl told police <PERSON> Rogers </PERSON> proposed marriage to her immediately after the attack. <PERSON> Rogers </PERSON> served 27 months in prison between June 1979 and January 1982. He also spent nine months in the <LOCATION> Oregon </LOCATION> <LOCATION> State </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Hospital </LOCATION> in 1974.
