 Typifying the growing cooperation of Roman Catholics and Protestants, the <ORGANIZATION> Metropolitan </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Synod </ORGANIZATION> of the <ORGANIZATION> Evangelical </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Lutheran </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Church </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> America </LOCATION> opened its three-day assembly Thursday with a celebration of Holy Communion in Roman Catholicism's St. Agnes Cathedral.
