<TEXT>
 Average airline fares have decreased at most major airports, with competition increasing substantially since deregulation a decade ago, according to an industry study. But another report, by the <ORGANIZATION> General </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Accounting </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Office </ORGANIZATION>, says airlines charge an average of 27 percent more per passenger mile on flights to and from 15 major hub airports than at other airports included in the study.
