<NOTE>By The Associated Press</NOTE>
<TEXT>
 The stock market closed moderately higher Tuesday after a choppy session marked by continued program trading and nervousness about the situation in <LOCATION> China </LOCATION>. The Dow Jones average of 30 industrials rose 15.62 points to 2,496.32. The price of gold shot up nearly $ 12 an ounce, while the dollar sagged. Bond prices finished mixed. Demand for precious metals increased because of the turmoil in <LOCATION> China </LOCATION>, driving up the price of gold and silver; cotton prices continued their slide; grain and soybean futures fell; livestock and pork prices declined; and oil futures were lower.
