 <ORGANIZATION> Hershey </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Foods </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> announced Wednesday it will build a $ 100 million chocolate factory near its existing plant here. Groundbreaking is set for late this summer for the plant, which will be about 130,000 square feet and process chocolate for the company's main factory. The new factory will have about 60 new employees. But start-up will mean a reduction of employees at the main factory as new machinery replaces older, less-efficient equipment, the company said. <ORGANIZATION> Hershey </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Foods </ORGANIZATION> President <PERSON> Kenneth </PERSON> <PERSON> Wolfe </PERSON> said it was not yet known how many employees at the main plant will be affected. But he said the company will try to ease job reductions through retraining and attrition.
