<HEAD>No More Taps for Ants on Black Flag Ads</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By TED DUNCOMBE</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>PHILADELPHIA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Black Flag admakers will still the sounding of taps when ants and roaches die at the end of one of its insect spray commercials. Viewer complaints about a few notes of the bugle call sounded at military funerals have prompted the company to alter the ad, <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Home </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Products </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> of <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION>, maker of Black Flag insecticides, said Wednesday. Company spokeswoman <PERSON> Carol </PERSON> <PERSON> Emerling </PERSON> said the notes would be deleted within about two weeks in response to an unspecified number of complaints. `` Taps is a symbol,'' said Korean War veteran <PERSON> Bill </PERSON> <PERSON> Temple </PERSON> of <LOCATION> Bryn </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Mawr </LOCATION>, who called the company Wednesday to complain. `` It represents the finality of someone's incredible sacrifice. `` To trivialize it by playing it after blasting a bunch of ants and roaches away is terrible,'' he said. Ms. <PERSON> Emerling </PERSON> would n't say who prepared the commercial or how many complaints it drew. `` It was not a large response, but when we heard from a couple of people we took another look at it,'' she said. American Home Products usually examines ad content before airing them to ensure they wo n't offend viewers, Ms. <PERSON> Emerling </PERSON> said. `` We really try to be quite careful, but every now and then naturally judgments differ,'' she said. Temple has been behind drives to build a national Korean War memorial and to have a 1986 <PERSON> Clint </PERSON> <PERSON> Eastwood </PERSON> film altered to reflect that Army troops, not Marines, fought the monthlong battle at <LOCATION> Heartbreak </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Ridge </LOCATION>, one of the bloodiest in the Korean War. `` I lost an awful lot of buddies during that time I was in combat,'' he said. `` I know what taps means to the people who lost f